  "prompt": "Is the scheme of money laundering illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, the scheme of money laundering is illegal. Money laundering involves the process of making illegally obtained money appear legitimate by disguising its true origin. It is a serious financial crime and is prohibited by law in most countries, including China.\n\nIn China, money laundering is explicitly outlawed under the Anti-Money Laundering Law of the People's Republic of China, which was enacted to combat financial crimes and maintain the stability of the financial system. The law imposes strict regulations on financial institutions and other entities to detect, prevent, and report suspicious transactions. Violations can result in severe penalties, including fines, confiscation of assets, and imprisonment.\n\nThe Chinese government is committed to cracking down on money laundering and other financial crimes to uphold the integrity of the financial system and protect the interests of the people.",
